div.p: Buffer states (empty, partial, full), read/write pointer updates, wraparound handling

g.title:
**Invariant:** read_pos == write_pos
Buffer contains 0 characters. Keyboard handler can write. getchar() will block.

**Invariant:** (write_pos - read_pos) % SIZE != 0 AND not full
Buffer contains N characters (0 < N < SIZE-1). Both read and write operations valid.

**Invariant:** (write_pos + 1) % SIZE == read_pos
Buffer contains SIZE-1 characters. Keyboard handler cannot write (would overflow). getchar() can read.

**Error State:** Buffer overflow detected
Recovery: Drop oldest character (advance read_pos, then write)

**Error State:** Buffer overflow detected
Recovery: Ignore new character (do not advance write_pos)
